# Architecture — Feature-based MVVM + Repository

Data flows in one direction:

```
View → Cubit (ViewModel) → Repository → DataSource
```

Each feature is self-contained under `lib/features/<feature>/` with `data/`, `view/`, and `viewModel/` sub-folders.
No Use Case layer by default — add one only when logic is shared across features or complex enough to test in isolation (see `use-cases.mdc`).

## Folder structure

```
lib/
├── app/                    # MyApp root widget
├── config/
│   ├── routes/             # AppRoutes (name constants) + AppRouter (GoRouter)
│   └── theme/              # AppColor, AppDimensions, AppTextStyle, AppTheme
├── core/
│   ├── di/                 # service_locator.dart + modules/<feature>_module.dart
│   ├── error/failure.dart  # ServerFailure / NetworkFailure / SystemFailure
│   ├── local/              # SessionManager (secure) + LocalDataSource (prefs)
│   └── network/            # ApiClient, ApiEndpoints, AuthInterceptor
├── features/<feature>/
│   ├── data/               # models/, datasources/, repositories/
│   ├── view/               # pages/, widgets/
│   └── viewModel/          # Cubits
├── services/firebase/      # FcmService
└── utils/                  # AppDialog, extensions, validators, states
```

## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | Does | Must NOT |
|---|---|---|
| **View** | Render UI, dispatch cubit calls, react in `BlocListener` | Business logic, repo/storage access |
| **Cubit** | Emit states, call repositories, manage session lifecycle | HTTP logic, JSON parsing, render UI |
| **Repository** | Parse `Response` → typed model, return `Either<Failure, T>` | Emit states, make UI decisions |
| **DataSource** | HTTP via `requestAPI()`, return raw `Either<Failure, Response>` | Parse JSON, know about models |
| **SessionManager** | Tokens + user JSON (FlutterSecureStorage) | Non-sensitive data, business logic |
| **LocalDataSource** | Non-sensitive prefs (SharedPreferences) | Sensitive data |

A Cubit may inject `SessionManager` directly **only** for session lifecycle (sign-in / logout). All other data goes through a Repository.

## Naming conventions

- Feature folders: `snake_case` (e.g. `user_profile`, `order_history`)
- Classes: `PascalCase` · Files: `snake_case.dart`
- Cubits in `viewModel/` · Pages in `view/pages/` · Widgets in `view/widgets/`

## Auth feature — demo only

`AuthRepository.signIn` returns stub data. Replace with a real `_dataSource.signIn(...)` call when connecting a backend. The rest of the auth scaffold (interceptor, session, routing) is production-ready.
